			<h2>Summary</h2>
			<p>Howdy, I am looking for a new challenge in my career. My skill set consists of over 20 years’ experience in land surveying, AutoCAD Civil design, GIS development, and project management. I have over 15 years of experience using Civil 3D, Carlson Survey, ArcGIS Pro, and others. I am fluent in most aspects of survey drafting and design in civil projects as well as oil and gas. Some examples of projects can include right-of- way centerline easements and descriptions, road, and highway crossing permits, cut and fill topo design drawings, alignment sheets, and boundary topo. I will be graduating at the end of this year with my master’s degree in geosciences with emphasis on GIS track at Texas A&M. I had the opportunity to build an internal GIS database for a survey company. This provided them with different tools to search and manage their data. I teach in the land surveying department mostly CAD classes but after I complete the degree, we will be creating a new GIS program at TJC. As of recently, I have started learning python programming, FME, and model building within ArcGIS Pro. I am available full-time during the summers (May-Aug) only. The remaining part of the year I can work later afternoons, evenings, and weekends. Remote will more than likely be the only option. Thanks for reading. </p><br>
			<h2>Skills</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><p>AutoCAD
          Skyline, ArcGIS Pro, Geodatabase Tools, Carlson Survey, Civil 3D, SolidWorks, Land Desktop, Global Mapper, Google Earth, Trimble Business Center, Adobe Bluebeam, MS Office Suite, Computer Repairs, and SmartPhone Repairs.</p>
