			<h2>Experience</h2>
			<h3>GIS Developer</h3>
			<p>Interland Surveying and Mapping</p>
			<p>April 2021 - Jan 2023</p>
			<ul>
				<p>This was a contract position to build a new GIS Database system for the survey company. I also helped manage the field data and base drawings while working with Trimble Business Center and Civil 3D 2020. This GIS is a management tool to search for control, monument, and boundary data within the company and access to other public data. I had plans to go further with the system to automate the daily tasks such as converting a data file from CAD to GIS format and then adding it to the database but unfortunately there were budget issues and the contract was put on hold.</p>
			</ul>
			<h3>Surveying AutoCAD Instructor</h3>
			<p>Tyler Junior College</p>
			<p>January 2015 - June 2018</p>
      <p>Prepare lecture notes and exercise descriptions, teaching, supervising practical exercises and student projects, for the Engineering Design and surveying students. The course subject consists of survey data collection, geo-data processing, topographic mapping, photo-and image mapping, geographic information systems, and civil engineering design procedures with 3D modeling. </p>
		  <h3>CAD Project Manager / Skyline Tech / IT Support</h3>
			<p>Transglobal Services, LLC</p>
			<p>April 2014 - April 2018</p>
      <p>Most of my duties at TGS were drafting centerline alignment sheets and easement plats. I was managing the CAD department for 2 of the clients. When I initially started, I assisted in as-built data development, AutoCAD standards, and GIS development for Anadarko and other clients.</p>
      <h3>Senior Survey Technician and GIS Analyst</h3>
			<p>Harris County Engineering</p>
			<p>Sep 2012 - April 2014</p>
      <p>Rebuilt the CAD drawing standards while streamlining the data processes. I Created boundary drawings, topographical and ALTA/ACSM surveys for engineering design support; Coordinate system and datum transformations; data conversion including converting CAD data to GIS and vice versa; geodatabase creation from spatial and non-spatial data (such as legal documents); spatial and attribute editing; georeferencing; cartographic design and map making for a variety of print and electronic formats; .kml creation for use with Google Earth; spatial analysis including raster calculation and analysis; raster data download and processing.</p>
      <h3>Survey Tech and GIS Analyst</h3>
			<p>RMC Surveying</p>
			<p>Sep 2008 - June 2012</p>
      <p>Created boundary drawings, topographical and ALTA/ACSM surveys for engineering design support and title insurance companies. Created plats for proposed Oil and Gas pipeline layouts. As-built pipeline platting and composed field notes for Anadarko Company and Chesapeake Energy. Plotted deeds and analyzed boundary lines for field to finish completion. Project managed over individual clients consisting mostly of residential lot improvement surveys.  Coordinate system and datum transformations; data conversion including converting CAD data to GIS and vice versa; geodatabase creation from spatial and non-spatial data (such as legal documents); spatial and attribute editing; digitizing; georeferencing; cartographic design and map making for a variety of print and electronic formats; .kml creation for use with Google Earth; spatial analysis including raster calculation and analysis; raster data download and processing.</p>
